Argentina has defaulted on its sovereign debt eight times since independence in 1816, 
spectacularly so in 2001 on $100bn of bonds - at the time the world's largest default. 

This year the peso lost 40% of its value, which led to President Macri requesting a $50bn loan from the IMF. 
Inspite of its poor credit history. 

Here's a simple chart, but memorable chart, depicting Argentina's shocking debt problems.

